  "title": "Core Concepts in Sex Education",
  "lessonText": "Understanding core concepts is essential for informed discussions about sex education.",
  "data": {
    "content": "- Sex education covers human anatomy and reproduction.\n- It emphasizes consent and healthy relationships.\n- Discussions include sexual orientation and gender identity.\n- Safe sex practices are crucial to prevent STIs and unintended pregnancies.\n- Communication skills are vital for discussing sexual health."
  }
}
